==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Infield
<hw>In*field"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To inclose, as a
field.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infield</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Infield
<hw>In"field`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Arable
and manured land kept continually under crop; -- distinguished from
<contr>outfield</contr>.</def> <mark>[Scotland]</mark>
<rj><au>Jamieson.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Baseball)</fld> <def>The diamond; -- opposed to
<contr>outfield</contr>. See <er>Diamond</er>, <pos>n.</pos>,
5.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>infighting</ent>⟦br⟧
